						               													<description>Cardwords is a word card game where each card has a letter and players spell words with them.  Both double deck and single deck versions have been published.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each deck has two copies of each letter of the alphabet, along with a point value of 1-4 points.  In all of the games playable with these decks, a duplicate letter can be used as a wild card standing for any letter, e.g. in &amp;quot;FFGHT&amp;quot;, since there are two 'F's one can be considered an 'I', spelling &amp;quot;FIGHT&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rules are included for seven games: &amp;#10;&amp;#10;    1: A fishing game like Logomachy (which is like Scopa), where a card played either combines with cards on the table to make a word, or is left on the table.&amp;#10;    2: Poker using words, either 5-card stud, 7-card stud or 5-card draw. &amp;#10;    3: Bingo, each player having a 3x3 array of cards, turning cards one at a time in any order (except the middle card last), with the first 3-letter word formed winning. &amp;#10;    4: Rummy, where players draw but never discard, laying down words from their hand or adding to words on the table, and the first player to play all their hand wins. &amp;#10;    5: Rummy, like #4 except a card is discarded at the end of each turn. &amp;#10;    6: Rummy, like #5 except that adding letters to a word lets you steal the word. &amp;#10;    7: Players start with 13-card hands, all players simultaneously pass a card to the left until one player announces having a word worth 15+ points and claims the pot. Then the player with the word gives one-word clues to their word until another player guesses their word, and the two split the second pot. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each game uses chips, with players adding chips to the pot during play, and the winner claiming the pot. Chips are not provided in the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
